    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - CHASSIS ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Two
        Speed Axle With Allison Electronic Automatic Transmission
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Two Speed Axle With Allison Electronic Automatic Transmission</title>
        <table id="t0823903" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Two Speed Axle With Allison Electronic Automatic Transmission</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.51in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.56in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.72in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.46in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Does two speed axle shift but speedometer does not reflect correct speed and
                                mileage?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 3.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect ECM conn. (379). Turn key on and with two speed switch in low position and
                                then high position, measure voltage from circuit 93A, pin 28 to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(379), 93A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts in low, 0 volts in high position.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Refer to Engine Diagnostic Manual for trouble- shoot- ing the ECM.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 93A or dash connector (2), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Check fuse F14 for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F14</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At fuse F14, Cavity A, measure voltage from circuit 12A to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>F14, cav. A, 12A to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re- install fuse. Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 12A, then repair. Re-install fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect dash conn. (13). Turn key on and with two speed switch in high position,
                                measure voltage from circuit 93C, cavity K1, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(13), 93C cav. K1, to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 11.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>on</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With two speed switch in low position and at (13), measure voltage from circuit 93B,
                                cavity K2, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(13), 93B, cav. K2, to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 11.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect conn. (13). Disconnect electric shift motor conn. (703) with electric shift,
                                or air shift solenoid conn. (N/L). Is axle equipped with an electric shift motor?
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 10.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>8.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At conn. (703), measure resistance of white wire to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(703), white wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in white wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>9.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At shift motor conn. (703), measure voltage from brown wire to ground with axle switch
                                in low position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(703), brown wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace shift motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in brown wire, then repair. If condition persists,
                                go to next step.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At electric shift motor (703) or air shift solenoid conn. (N/L), measure voltage from
                                red wire to ground with two speed axle switch in high position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(730), or air sol. conn., red wire to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace electric shift motor or air shift solenoid.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in red wire, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect two speed relay (488). Turn key on and at relay socket, measure voltage
                                from circuit 93G, cavity E/1, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(488), 93G cav. E/1 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuits 93G, 93E, 93 or inline conn. (495) or
                                two speed harness conn. (14), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>With two speed sw. in high position and at relay socket (488), measure voltage from
                                circuit 93G, cavity E/1, to circuit 93D, cavity A/5.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(488), 93G cav. E/1, to 93D cav. A/5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>If Step 5 failed, go to next step. If Step 6 failed, go to Step 14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to Step 15.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>13.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (488) install jumper from circuit 93G, cavity E/1, to circuit 93C, cavity D/3. Turn
                                key on and at dash conn. (13), measure voltage from circuit 93C, cavity K1, to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(13), 93C cav. K1 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 93C or connectors (495) or (14), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>14.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (488) move jumper end from circuit 93C, cavity D/3, to circuit 93B, cavity C/4.
                                Turn key on and at dash conn. (13), measure voltage from circuit 93B, cavity K2, to
                                ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(13), 93B cav. K2 to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 93B on connectors (495) or (14), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>15.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (488), install jumper from circuit 93D, cavity A/5 to ground. Disconnect ECU
                                input/output conn. (466). At (466), measure resistance from circuit 93D to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(466), 93D to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 93D, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>16.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (466), measure resistance from circuit 93F to 93 with two speed switch in low
                                position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(466), 93F to 93.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuits 93F or 93, or connector (495) or two speed
                                switch (75), then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>17.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At (466), measure resistance from circuit 93F to 93 with two speed switch in high
                                position.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>(466), 93F to 93.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace two speed switch.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>18.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect connectors and relay. Two speed axle shift circuits check good. If condition
                                persists, refer problem to an authorized Allison dealer.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
